1. *Optuženi* je priznao krivicu. (The accused admitted guilt.)
2. Advokat je branio *optuženog* u sudnici. (The lawyer defended the accused in court.)
3. *Optužena* je dobila kaznu zatvora. (The accused woman received a prison sentence.)
4. Tužilac je podigao optužnicu protiv *optuženih*. (The prosecutor brought charges against the accused.)
5. *Optuženima* se sudi za teško ubistvo. (The accused are being tried for a serious murder.)
6. Policija je uhapsila *optuženog* za krađu. (The police arrested the accused for theft.)
7. Sudija je oslobodio *optuženog* zbog nedostatka dokaza. (The judge acquitted the accused for lack of evidence.)
8. Advokati *optuženih* su tražili odlaganje suđenja. (The accused's lawyers requested a postponement of the trial.)
9. *Optuženi* se nije pojavio na sudu. (The accused did not appear in court.)
10. Sud je proglasio *optuženog* krivim za prevaru. (The court found the accused guilty of fraud.)

Note: In Serbian, the word "optuženi" can be used as a noun, adjective, or in the genitive, dative, accusative, or instrumental case, depending on the sentence structure and context.